						<summary>

						<p>On a slab lying infront of Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p>Telugu Chōḍa; Veṁkeya Chōḷa Mahārāju 41st regnal year, Chaitra śu. 10, Sunday.</p>						

						<p>It commences with the <hi rend="italic">prasasti</hi> Svasti charaṇa sarōruha etc. and records the gift of land to the goddess Kuṟuva Bhaṭāri by the king who bears the titles like <hi rend="italic">Teṅkaṇāditya Komara-Bhīma.</hi> In characters about 9th-10th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.,</hi> Vol. XXXIII, pp. 27-30, plate.]</p>						

						</summary>
